original_title: Brooklyn: New Lots Avenue - Church Avenue
text:
(1) New Lots Road, south side, west of Church Ave., showing the Derick Remsen house. April 1926. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, showing the barn being demolished. It was located at the N.E. corner of Church Ave., and Rockaway Parkway. January 26, 1927. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3) The same, showing the barn, partially demolished, and the house razed. Also seen is the side of the William F. Ryerson house. January 26, 1927. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(4) The same, another view. E.L. Armbruster, the photographer, states that one Van Brunt, who took down this house, intends to move it to a place believed to be Westchester County. January 26, 1927. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
